reviews.title: Delicious lunch in beautiful place
reviews.text:
During the summer holidays I ate at Floor with my husband and children aged 11 and 13. It is a beautiful place in the woods and we sat in the shade on the terrace. 
Inside it is also very atmospheric and even the toilet rooms look nice. 

The service was friendly and visited regularly. I ordered a glass of wine and was asked if I wanted a glass of water with it. We do not recognize ourselves in the negative reviews. 

The oldest venison steak ordered with green asparagus and sweet potato, medium rare, this one was perfectly prepared.  He would have liked more than two asparagus and the sweet potato was a kind of sauce/mash. It was for the big appetite but fries had to be ordered separately. For big appetites, I would expect there to be a little more. It was lovely beyond that, not of that. 
My husband and I both had it 12 hours, because we couldn't choose. Eggs Benedict with salmon, potato salad, bread with ribeye, soup (he pea-cream and I leek conté), everything was very tasty and flavorful. 
The youngest had the Floor burger, which was also very tasty. The children still had room for dessert, the pineapple tarte tatin and the parfait went down well. 
We tasted everything from each other, and agreed that we would love to come back sometime. 

It is not the cheapest lunch, but a menu with less standard dishes than you usually see and in a beautiful place, we like that.

reviews.title: This restaurant does not know what hospitality means
reviews.text:
This afternoon December 1st I went here to have lunch
Was neatly assigned a table
However after 5 minutes I woke someone to order a drink and ask for the card
I got this pretty quick
Only after 15 minutes came the genius idea if I wanted to order some food
You understand it didn't have to be for me anymore
Indicated that I felt I was being treated shamefully and why
I also indicated if she wanted to pass this on to the floor manager
Saw her do this too 
After that no excuses from the floor manager 
You'll never see me here again

reviews.title: relaxed food at Floor.
reviews.text:
Brasserie Floor. A cozy place to have a bite to eat in a casual and relaxed setting. Dogs are also welcome here, a big plus.

Floor is located on a main road in nature on the edge of Epe. Spacious parking space at the front. There is a large terrace to sit outside when the weather is nice. The interior is pleasantly decorated. Fireplace, nice chairs and table. A bit of a lounge-like feeling. It is a more elegant occasion. You can see this in the decor, the dishes on the menu (and associated prices) and the whole. You can just go in with your dirty shoes. But there were also plenty of dressed up people having lunch. So not your average "mud on the floor" forest cafe with only walkers.

There are many tasty things on the menu. Soups, bouncers, sandwiches. We had already finished our treats and then we saw a well-stocked snack board passing by, and we regretted that we had not chosen that one. It is a nice place to sit and relax with a snack and drink after a walk.

The service is friendly and correct. Adjusting a dish slightly to your taste is no problem. Reservations are not necessary. When we were there and had a nice meal, we noticed that it could get a lot busier inside at certain times. So you might have to wait a while for a spot.

The menu is extensive, the dishes look good and taste delicious. In addition to bread with tuna melt, bouncer, and soup, the menu also includes bread with croquettes, salads and prawns. The only comment is that the ratio of coffee and tea is a bit skewed. Very small cups of coffee and the tea seems like a lot until you take out the tea strainer. The price / quantity is a bit skewed because how much does a glass of hot water cost?

All in all a very pleasant experience and delicious food.

reviews.title: Floor Brasserie
reviews.text: The fact that such a beautiful gem full of delicacies is located in the middle of the forest makes the experience complete. There is a friendly atmosphere, hospitality at its best and everything that came along looked good and luckily what we ordered was also very tasty. Highly recommended

reviews.title: Unsociable and not really special
reviews.text:
We had to wait quite a long time for the starters and main courses. The presentation of the dishes looks nice, but it lacks taste. It's all a bit bland. In one of the dishes the mother of pearl was already lukewarm and therefore cold after a few minutes. Not really tasty.
I can imagine that it is wonderful to drink coffee here in the spring and summer during a cycling or walking tour, but dining is not for us here.

tripContent.title: Orlando: An LGBTQ+ family guide

reviews.title: Nice location, very good food
reviews.text: Floor is located in the forrest. After a warm welcome we got a nice table. They offer daily specials and a regular menu. All dishes we had were excellent. Lamb, gambas or steak, everything a good choice. Young service, friendly and competent. We will for sure come back.

reviews.title: Nice and normal
reviews.text: We had an nice walk trough the woods walking toward the restaurant. Not a very big menu but big enough. The food was nice, so was the service. The wine we choose was not bad but for the price we paid I aspected a better wine, a bit of a dissapointment.

reviews.title: good value for money
reviews.text: finding an open place for dinner in rural Netherlands is not easy. so we drove some 20 minutes to Epe, saw nothing was open in town and ended at Floor. were attended by a young English speaking waiter who was very helpful. had excellent onion soup and tomato soup, and main courses of fish were nice.

reviews.title: Nicely located, but lousy service
reviews.text: The environment in the woods is very beautiful. This place has recently be refurbished and looks very attractive. The menu, though simple is very good, and well-prepared. The personnel however, excel in the dutch "no-style at all" approach, treating the client as a friend, whereas I am not. They lack knowledge, in respect of the simple menu and its contents as well as any formal etiquette. If you enjoy being treated as the next door's client, by all means, otherwise this place is a waist of time.

reviews.title: A must
reviews.text: Excellent ambiance and food. People are so friendly and open minded and always ready to help you. The interior is so nice decorated. Also you can buy very nice things for @home

reviews.title: Definitely worth visiting
reviews.text: We realised that this is owned by the same couple that have the Dennenheuvel Hotel in Epe so we wanted to see if the same quality had been established.  It has.  Service is very friendly and the staff are good.  Food is also very good.  Interior design is thoughtful and well done.  Sitting outside at a table in the sun, among all the trees - magic.  We came back down one week later from Amsterdam just to eat here again.
